Beltane is Here 🔥 An Epic Druidic Collaboration with the Brilliant Fantasy Folk Vocalist and Composer @bartzealmusic. Three Versions, streaming everywhere 🎶🙏🔥

Beltane also known as May day is a pagan ritual celebrating the height of spring. A cross quarter day celebrating the halfway mark between Spring Equinox and Summer Solstice. 

Bonfires have been a part of beltane rituals for generations, dancing around fire and rejoicing in the wonders of the season. 

Beltane in Celtic means “lucky fire.”

Many of you have asked how we composed Blades of the forest and which libraries we used. Here's a short information about the inspiration but also about our way of working and libraries we used: 

This piece was inspired from the incredible game score of Ilan Eshkeri, Shigeru Umebayashi’s Ghost of Tsushima, and Tan Dun, Yo-Yo Ma’s Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon. 87 total tracks covering every element of the orchestral spectrum. The key to mixing this piece was finding space for the many layers of instruments. Creative stereo panning and EQ manipulation were integral in every track to let each instrument have its own unique voice. 

Eric put together the melodic elements and built a foundation for the composition. Juliano brought in an entire orchestra creating the epic depth and climaxes throughout the piece

New 🎹 Project “Mistborn” 🎶 

Taking inspiration from one my favorite novels, here is a demo of a live recording session.  I wanted to show a bit of my process for how I layer the orchestral instruments.  In this piece, I started with the grand piano, added an ambient piano harmony over the top, followed by low strings and a cello line.  Violins and double bass pizzicatos were next, and finished off with a French horn. 

Stay tuned for the final version of this piece coming later this fall :) 

Sounds used
Intimate Grand Piano @spitfireaudio 
Ólafur Felt Piano @spitfireaudio 
Lumina Con Sordino Strings @projectsam_libs 
Tina Guo Cello @cinesamples 
Double Bass Novo Strings @heavyocity 
Josh Bell Violin @embertonesounds 
French Horn @cinesamples

Like any epic road you’d find in Iceland, there was this one that found me.  I stood here for some time considering the expanse before me. I remember thinking if it wasn’t for the massive rocks and mountains that seemed to go on forever, the blue of the ocean and the blue of the sky would bleed together. Don’t ever let anyone tell you there isn’t more to see in this world that is amazing. More that will change you for the better. May the wind be always At your back.
May the sun shine warm Oh, may it greet you.
May the rain fall soft Across the land,
Until we meet again! 

Until We Meet Again tells the story of two companions on a harrowing and perilous journey to reunite.

Bart composed the lyrics and arranged the vocal lines and Eric created the orchestral foundation for the piece. 

This piece was mastered brilliantly by @machinetheproducer
